text.tspan: Chip is square, shown as a breakout.
The notation RX.1 is alternate position so Serial.swap(). You must choose RX.1 and TX.1 or RX and TX together (exception: TCA).
Signals are often suffixed by the peripheral number so RX1 is UART1 rx. In a few cases n,FN is used (2,OUT.1).
Data from ATtiny1616 dfp.3.0.151. Diagrams by ObviousInRetrospect.
